On May 30th, the church released the first batch of new hymns. I have done posts on how those hymns have been used during the [first](posts/new_hymns_week1), [second](posts/new_hymns_week2), and [third](posts/new_hymns_week3) weeks since their release, but this page covers the 15 weeks between when the first and second batches came out. When I get more data from this period I will update this page, but it will largely remain as is. Currently I have data from 2,731 sacrament meetings between June 2nd and September 8th from 725 wards. For now, I'll just focus on hymns 1001--1009 and will wait to bring in the new holiday hymns later on.

But first, here's how much data I have for each week, just so you have an idea of what I'm working with.



